         <div type="transcription">
            <p><milestone unit="passage" n="Poṣatha (Uposatha)"/>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><foreign xml:lang="san"><w><supplied>āy</supplied>u<supplied>ṣ</supplied>m<supplied>aṃ</supplied></w><w>dh<supplied>ā</supplied>r<supplied>a</supplied>ya</w><w>antarāyi<supplied>keṣu</supplied></w><w><supplied>dharmeṣu</supplied></w><w><supplied>pariśuddhaṃ</supplied></w><w><supplied>ahaṃ</supplied></w></foreign>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><foreign xml:lang="san"><w><supplied>poṣathaṃ</supplied></w><w>kariṣyāmi</w><w>śīlaskandhasya</w><w><supplied>pāripūraye</supplied></w><w><supplied>evaṃ</supplied></w><w><supplied>dvir</supplied></w><w><supplied>api</supplied></w><w><supplied>tṛr</supplied></w><w><supplied>api</supplied></w><pc><supplied>॥</supplied></pc></foreign>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>s<supplied>e</supplied></w><w>triwācik</w><w>posāt</w><pc>।</pc><pc>।</pc><w><supplied>ñ</supplied>i<supplied>ś</supplied></w><w><supplied>t</supplied>e<supplied>-ñemtsa</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a4"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="5"/><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>ā</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="6"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="9"/><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>te</supplied>śit</w><w>yāmtsisa</w><pc>॥</pc><foreign xml:lang="san"><w>samanv<supplied>ā</supplied>h<supplied>arāyuṣmāṃ</supplied></w><w><supplied>adya</supplied></w><w><supplied>saṃghasya</supplied></w></foreign>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><gap reason="lost"/><foreign xml:lang="san"><w><supplied>poṣatha</supplied></w><w>pāñcadaśika</w><w>ahaṃ</w><w>bhikṣu</w><w>dhā<supplied>rmikeṣu</supplied></w><w><supplied>saṃghakarmaṇi</supplied></w><w><supplied>cchandaṃ</supplied></w></foreign>
<lb corresp="#b4"/><gap reason="lost"/><foreign xml:lang="san"><w><supplied>dadāmi</supplied></w><w><supplied>anum</supplied>o<supplied>dām</supplied>i</w><w>abhyupagacch<supplied>āmi</supplied></w></foreign><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl"><hi>Sanskrit</hi></seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl"><hi>Sanskrit</hi></seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">This is the Uposatha [ceremony] effected by three words. | | I named such and such ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">By making confession (deśita-) || <hi>Sanskrit</hi> </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl"><hi>Sanskrit</hi></seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl"><hi>Sanskrit</hi></seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment">The lines a1 to a2 have a parallel in the Sanskrit text IOL San 400 (=Ch. 00262.9), cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:lavalleepoussin1913"/><citedRange>846</citedRange></bibl>, so do the lines b1 to b3, cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:hartel1956"/><citedRange>109</citedRange></bibl> (§69).</note><note type="philcomment">As for the Tocharian part, line a3 corresponds to the one on the London fragment IOL San 400 a3 <hi>se trivācik posāt</hi>. The lines b2 to b3 have a parallel in the Sanskrit text IOL 400 a3 and a4 up to <hi>pāñcadaśika</hi>; afterwards there is a different text.</note><note type="philcomment">Starting from <hi>ahaṃ bhikṣu</hi> the line b3 to b4 have a parallel in the Sanskrit text IOL San 404 (=Ch. 00262.10) a2 to a3, cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:lavalleepoussin1913"/><citedRange>846</citedRange></bibl> and the text restored by <bibl><title corresp="ref:hartel1956"/><citedRange>117</citedRange></bibl> (§79, 2). Note that the Sanskrit form <hi>anumodāmi</hi> is incorrect for the expected middle <hi>anumode</hi> 'I approve'.</note><note type="remarks">This tiny fragment belongs to the same manuscript as <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-pkns124"/> and IOL San 400 and 404.</note></p>
         </div>
