               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;The lines a1 to a2 have a parallel in the Sanskrit text IOL San 400 (=Ch. 00262.9), cf. [[La Vallée Poussin 1913]]: 846, so do the lines b1 to b3, cf. [[Härtel 1956]]: 109 (§69).&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;As for the Tocharian part, line a3 corresponds to the one on the London fragment IOL San 400 a3 &lt;i&gt;se trivācik posāt&lt;/i&gt;. The lines b2 to b3 have a parallel in the Sanskrit text IOL 400 a3 and a4 up to &lt;i&gt;pāñcadaśika&lt;/i&gt;; afterwards there is a different text.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Starting from &lt;i&gt;ahaṃ bhikṣu&lt;/i&gt; the line b3 to b4 have a parallel in the Sanskrit text IOL San 404 (=Ch. 00262.10) a2 to a3, cf. [[La Vallée Poussin 1913]]: 846 and the text restored by [[Härtel 1956]]: 117 (§79, 2). Note that the Sanskrit form &lt;i&gt;anumodāmi&lt;/i&gt; is incorrect for the expected middle &lt;i&gt;anumode&lt;/i&gt; 'I approve'.&lt;/p&gt;</item>
